The paper discusses a novel surgical perception framework for surgical robotic control, which involves collecting 3D geometric information to map a deformable surgical field while tracking rigid instruments within the field. This involves the use of model-based and model-free trackers to achieve the desired results. Given the focus on robotics and computer vision, as well as the use of machine learning techniques, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). However, the paper also involves computer vision techniques such as 3D reconstruction and tracking, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the use of machine learning techniques for tracking and control suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the focus on control and regulation of the surgical tool suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
